This is a letter from President Barack Obama to the congressional committee leadership, specifically the chairmen and ranking members of the House and Senate committees on Armed Services and Appropriations, as well as the chairmen and ranking members of the House Committee on Foreign Affairs and the Senate Committee on Foreign Relations. The letter is in response to the requirement of section 1116 of the Supplemental Appropriations Act, 2009, and it provides a report related to Afghanistan and Pakistan. The President assures the committee leadership that his administration has completed a thorough policy review and announced a new approach in December. The administration believes that no further adjustments are required at this time and is committed to the successful implementation of this policy.